Assessment for mutation burden in endometrial glands

Markdown file to present the methods to examine mutational burden in endometrial glands. Before you start the following analyses, please convert the corresponding excel source data files to tab-delimited text files. The source data files are provided in our paper (Yamaguchi et al. Nat Commun in press).

Visualize mutation burden in endometrial glands

mutBurd_long <- mutBurd %>% gather(key="substitution", value="burden", -subject, -age, -cum_num_menstrual_cycles, -pack_years, -total)

mutBurd_long$substitution2 <- sub("^burden_", "", mutBurd_long$substitution)
mutBurd_long$substitution3 <- sub("\\.", ">", mutBurd_long$substitution2)
mutBurd_long$substitution4 <- factor(mutBurd_long$substitution3,
  levels = c("C>T", "C>A", "C>G", "T>C", "T>G", "T>A"))

subject_order <- mutBurd[order(mutBurd$total), ]$subject
mutBurd_long$subject2 <- factor(mutBurd_long$subject, levels=subject_order)

mycolors <- c("#E62725", "#1EBFF0", "#050708", "#A1CF64", "#EDC8C5", "#CBCACB")

p_burd <- ggplot(mutBurd_long, aes(fill=substitution4, col=substitution4, x=subject2, y=burden)) 
p_burd <- p_burd + geom_bar(position="stack", stat="identity")
p_burd <- p_burd + scale_fill_manual(values=mycolors, name="")
p_burd <- p_burd + scale_colour_manual(values=mycolors, name="")
p_burd <- p_burd + theme(
  axis.ticks=element_blank(), 
  axis.text.x=element_text(size=10, colour="black", angle=90, hjust=0, vjust=0.5), 
  axis.text.y=element_text(size=20, colour="black"), 
  axis.title=element_text(size=20), 
  legend.text=element_text(size=20), 
  legend.position=c(0.1, 0.8),
  panel.grid.major=element_blank(),
  panel.border=element_blank(),
  panel.background=element_blank())
p_burd <- p_burd + xlab("")
p_burd <- p_burd + ylab("Number of somatic SNVs\nper Mb sequenced")

plot(p_burd)

Visualize linear relationships between age and mutation burdens stratified by substitution types

mycolors2 = c("#E62725", "#1EBFF0", "#050708", "#A1CF64", "#EDC8C5", "#CBCACB")

p_age <- ggplot(mutBurd_long, aes(x=age, y=burden, fill=substitution4))
p_age <- p_age + geom_smooth(method="lm", level=0.95, color="black", size=0.5)
p_age <- p_age + geom_point(aes(fill=substitution4), shape=21, colour="black", size=5, alpha=0.9)
p_age <- p_age + facet_wrap(~ substitution4, nrow=2, ncol=3)
p_age <- p_age + ylim(0, max(mutBurd_long$burden))
p_age <- p_age + xlab("Age")
p_age <- p_age + ylab("Number of somatic SNVs\nper Mb sequenced")
p_age <- p_age + scale_fill_manual(values=mycolors2) 
p_age <- p_age + scale_colour_manual(values=mycolors2) 
p_age <- p_age + theme(
  legend.position="none", 
  axis.line=element_line(colour="#d3d3d3"),
  panel.grid.major=element_line(colour="#d3d3d3"),
  panel.grid.minor=element_blank(),
  panel.border=element_blank(), 
  panel.background=element_blank(),
  axis.ticks=element_blank(), 
  axis.text.x=element_text(size=20, colour="black"), 
  axis.text.y=element_text(size=20, colour="black"), 
  axis.title=element_text(size=20), 
  strip.text.x=element_text(size=20, colour="white"), 
  strip.text.y=element_text(size=20), 
  strip.background=element_rect(fill="black"))

plot(p_age)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Pearson correlation coefficients between age and mutation burdens stratified by substitution types

subst <- c("C>T", "C>A", "C>G", "T>C", "T>G", "T>A")
r_coef <- vector(mode="numeric", length(subst))
p_value <- vector(mode="numeric", length(subst))

for (i in 1:length(subst)) {
  temp_data <- mutBurd_long[mutBurd_long$substitution4 == subst[i], ]
  res <- cor.test(temp_data$age, temp_data$burden)
  r_coef[i] <- res$estimate
  p_value[i] <- res$p.value
}

result_age <- data.frame(
  substitution=subst,
  r=r_coef,
  p_value=p_value)

result_age
